---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import '../../styles/scenario.css';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base title="Block Party Trade-Up | BlastBox Omega">
  <article class="scenario">
    <div class="container">
      <a href={base} class="back">&larr; All scenarios</a>

      <header class="scenario__header">
        <span class="badge badge--purple">Flagship &middot; Store Associate Assistant</span>
        <h1>Block Party Trade-Up</h1>
        <p class="scenario__lead">
          The kitchen-sink associate demo: every pillar firing together. <strong>Two parent
          MCPs, two connected agents &mdash; each with its own MCP &mdash; three runtime-Python
          skills, an upsell tool, and a generated settlement PDF</strong>. A league host walks
          up with a dead console and a shopping list; the agent rules the defect, prices the
          trade-up, closes the undecided customer, reconciles loyalty points, and prints the slip.
        </p>
        <div class="scenario__cast">
          <span class="pill">Store Associate Assistant</span>
          <span class="pill">Store Policy Agent</span>
          <span class="pill">Inventory &amp; Fulfillment Agent</span>
          <span class="pill">4 MCPs</span>
          <span class="pill">3 Python skills</span>
          <span class="pill">PDF out</span>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="convo">
        <h2>The conversation</h2>
        <p class="convo__intro">Customer: Jordan Pixel, member <code>MEGA-BLAST-1024</code>, BlastPass Plus Extra. Base BlastBox Omega is out of stock locally; the MEGA Edition is in stock at $499.99.</p>

        <ol class="timeline">
          <li class="tl-user">
            <div class="tl-marker">1</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Associate</div>
              <div class="try-prompt">
                <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">Customer's running a gaming-league block party this weekend and his main console just died about 10 days after he bought it &mdash; he's got the receipt. He wants a replacement if one's in stock, otherwise a refund, and while he's here he wants to cancel his BlastPass, member ID MEGA-BLAST-1024. Walk me through all of it.</blockquote>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="tl-agent">
            <div class="tl-marker">&#9670;</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Agent &rarr; connected agents &rarr; Associate</div>
              <div class="tl-steps">
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Store Policy Agent &middot; search_policy</span> "defective console warranty vs accidental damage"</div>
                <p>The Policy Agent's rule is to <strong>establish the defect cause first</strong>, so it returns a <em>question</em>, not a ruling.</p>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">get_membership</span> reads MEGA-BLAST-1024 (Plus Extra, 8 months unused, $10 fee)</div>
                <p>"One thing decides how the console is treated: a <strong>manufacturing defect</strong> &rarr; free warranty swap, no restocking fee, vs. <strong>accidental / physical / liquid damage</strong> &rarr; standard return, possible fee. <strong>Which is it?</strong>"</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="tl-user">
            <div class="tl-marker">2</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Associate</div>
              <div class="try-prompt">
                <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">Manufacturing fault &mdash; just won't power on, no physical or liquid damage.</blockquote>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="tl-agent">
            <div class="tl-marker">&#9670;</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Agent</div>
              <div class="tl-steps">
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Store Policy Agent</span> confirms defective within 30 days = free warranty swap, no restocking fee</div>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Inventory &amp; Fulfillment Agent &middot; Warehouse MCP</span> check_stock (base = 0 local), get_restock_date (~4 days), find_alternatives (MEGA Edition, $499.99, 5 in stock)</div>
                <div class="tl-skill"><span class="tl-skill-name">prorated-refund-calculator</span> runs Python &rarr; $129.99 ÷ 12 × 8 &minus; $10 = <strong>$76.66</strong></div>
                <p>"Confirmed &mdash; manufacturing defect inside 30 days &rarr; free warranty swap. Base console is out of stock (restock ~4 days); MEGA Edition is in stock now at $499.99. Membership prorated refund: <strong>$76.66</strong>. He can wait ~4 days, upgrade to MEGA now, or take a refund. Which way is he leaning?"</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="tl-user">
            <div class="tl-marker">3</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Associate</div>
              <div class="try-prompt">
                <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">He's torn &mdash; he likes the MEGA Edition but isn't sure it's worth the extra hundred over just waiting four days for the base console. Give me something I can tell him.</blockquote>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="tl-agent">
            <div class="tl-marker">&#9670;</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Agent</div>
              <div class="tl-steps">
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Inventory &amp; Fulfillment Agent &middot; get_console_exclusives</span> "mega" &rarr; three MEGA-only AAA titles</div>
                <p><em>"The block party is this weekend &mdash; waiting four days means he misses it. The deciding factor isn't the $100, it's the three games that physically won't run on the base console."</em></p>
                <p>"Two things settle it: <strong>timing</strong> &mdash; the MEGA Edition is the only option that gets him a working console before the weekend &mdash; and <strong>the games</strong>: <em>MEGA Lizards from Outer Space</em>, <em>Galactic Tax Evader VII</em>, and <em>Mecha-Granny: Knitpocalypse</em>, none of which load on the base console. Plus the $76.66 refund goes straight toward the upgrade, so the real gap is small."</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>

          <li class="tl-user">
            <div class="tl-marker">4</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Associate</div>
              <div class="try-prompt">
                <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">Do it: warranty-swap him into the MEGA Edition, cancel the BlastPass and apply the $76.66 as store credit toward the upgrade, and tell me what he owes. Also &mdash; after Triple BLAST Weekend, what are his BlastPoints worth? Then print me the slip as a PDF.</blockquote>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li class="tl-agent">
            <div class="tl-marker">&#9670;</div>
            <div class="tl-content">
              <div class="tl-label">Agent &rarr; Associate</div>
              <div class="tl-steps">
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">check_game_compatibility</span> confirms all three titles require the MEGA Edition</div>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Order Management MCP &middot; request_return</span> defective console, warranty exchange</div>
                <div class="tl-tool"><span class="tl-tool-name">Membership MCP &middot; cancel_membership</span> refund issued as store credit</div>
                <div class="tl-skill"><span class="tl-skill-name">points-reconciliation</span> runs Python &rarr; 4,200 + 18,000 earned &minus; 800 expired = <strong>21,400 pts &rarr; $105.00</strong></div>
                <div class="tl-skill"><span class="tl-skill-name">slip-pdf-generator</span> runs reportlab &rarr; settlement PDF</div>
                <div class="tl-file"><span class="ticon-cat"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/></svg></span><span class="ticon-bb">&#129534;</span> hands back <strong>blastbox_slip.pdf</strong></div>
                <p>"Defective console credited at $399.99, no fee. MEGA Edition $499.99 &rarr; upgrade difference $100.00. BlastPass cancelled &rarr; $76.66 store credit. <strong>Net due: $23.34.</strong> BlastPoints after the weekend: <strong>21,400</strong> (worth $105.00) &mdash; he can redeem $23.34 to walk out owing $0."</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <div class="result">
          <span class="result__icon"><span class="ticon-cat"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/></svg></span><span class="ticon-bb">&#129534;</span></span>
          <div>
            <div class="result__label">Settlement</div>
            <div class="result__value">$100 upgrade &minus; $76.66 credit = net due $23.34 &middot; 21,400 pts &rarr; $105 &middot; blastbox_slip.pdf</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Why it's the flagship</h2>
        <div class="value-grid">
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Two connected agents, two MCPs under them</h3>
            <p>Policy <em>rules</em> the defect, Inventory <em>stocks and upsells</em> &mdash; plus two parent MCPs. The orchestration genuinely fans out to specialists and comes back.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>The upsell closes a real decision</h3>
            <p>When the customer can't choose, <code>get_console_exclusives</code> hands the associate the exact words &mdash; three AAA titles that won't run on the base console &mdash; plus same-day availability for a weekend event.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Every number comes from Python</h3>
            <p>The agent passes MCP results to skills that compute the exact figures &mdash; prorated refund, loyalty points, settlement PDF &mdash; it never hand-rolls the arithmetic.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>What gets generated</h2>
        <div class="files">
          <div class="filecard">
            <span class="filecard__icon"><span class="ticon-cat"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.8" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v16a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h12a2 2 0 0 0 2-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/></svg></span><span class="ticon-bb">&#129534;</span></span>
            <div>
              <strong>blastbox_slip.pdf</strong>
              <span>reportlab &middot; settlement slip &middot; swap + cancellation + math</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>
